<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Compliance Freeze Request — Case {{ case_id }}</title>
{% include "_styles.html.j2" %}
</head>
<body{% if draft %} class="draft" data-draft-label="{{ draft_label | default('DRAFT') }}"{% endif %}>

<section class="cover">
  <div class="cover-letterhead">
    <div class="cover-wordmark">
      Recupero
      <span class="tagline">Investigation Services</span>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-letterhead-right">
      <div class="confidential">Strictly Private &amp; Confidential</div>
      <div class="date">{{ generated_at }} UTC</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cover-title-block">
    {# v0.14.9: branch the cover framing on the evidence shape. #}
    {% if issuer_freezable and issuer_freezable.evidence_mode == "historical_only" %}
    <div class="cover-eyebrow">Investigative Compliance Request</div>
    <h1>Compliance<br/>Freeze Request</h1>
    <p class="cover-subtitle">
      On-chain tracing confirms that {{ issuer_freezable.token }} issued by
      {{ issuer.short_name }} was received at
      {{ issuer_freezable.historical_count }}
      {{ "wallet" if issuer_freezable.historical_count == 1 else "wallets" }}
      identified below as part of a documented theft. Current balances at
      those addresses may or may not still hold the funds. We respectfully
      request that {{ issuer.short_name }} (a) place a precautionary hold
      on any remaining balance, and (b) provide investigative cooperation
      regarding the disposition of the {{ issuer_freezable.token }}
      received — namely, the deposit history at any
      {{ issuer.short_name }}-controlled account that received funds from
      these addresses, and any onward transfers your records reflect.
    </p>
    <div class="cover-rule"></div>
    {% elif issuer_freezable and issuer_freezable.evidence_mode == "mixed" %}
    <div class="cover-eyebrow">Time-Sensitive Compliance Matter</div>
    <h1>Compliance<br/>Freeze Request</h1>
    <p class="cover-subtitle">
      Stolen funds traced from the victim's wallet were received at
      {{ issuer_freezable.total_count }} {{ "wallet" if issuer_freezable.total_count == 1 else "wallets" }}
      under {{ issuer.short_name }}'s issuance authority. Of these,
      {{ issuer_freezable.current_balance_count }} reflect current-balance
      evidence (precautionary freeze requested) and
      {{ issuer_freezable.historical_count }} reflect historical-inflow
      evidence (investigative cooperation requested in addition to any
      freeze action on remaining balance). Both classes are documented in
      section 4 below.
    </p>
    <div class="cover-rule"></div>
    {% elif issuer_freezable %}
    <div class="cover-eyebrow">Time-Sensitive Compliance Matter</div>
    <h1>Compliance<br/>Freeze Request</h1>
    <p class="cover-subtitle">
      Stolen funds traced from the victim's wallet have been laundered
      into {{ issuer_freezable.token }} and are currently held at
      {{ issuer_freezable.total_count }} {{ "wallet" if issuer_freezable.total_count == 1 else "wallets" }}
      under {{ issuer.short_name }}'s issuance authority. We respectfully
      request a voluntary precautionary freeze pending law-enforcement
      engagement.
    </p>
    <div class="cover-rule"></div>
    {% else %}
    <div class="cover-eyebrow">Time-Sensitive Compliance Matter</div>
    <h1>Compliance<br/>Freeze Request</h1>
    <p class="cover-subtitle">
      A stolen {{ asset.symbol }} position is currently held in an
      identifiable wallet under {{ issuer.short_name }}'s issuance
      authority. We respectfully request a voluntary precautionary
      freeze pending law-enforcement engagement.
    </p>
    <div class="cover-rule"></div>
    {% endif %}
  </div>

  <dl class="cover-meta">
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Addressed To</dt>
      <dd>{{ issuer.name }}<span class="secondary">Compliance &amp; Security<br/>{{ issuer.contact_email }}</span></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Prepared By</dt>
      <dd>{{ investigator.name }}<span class="secondary">{{ investigator.organization }}<br/>on behalf of {{ victim.name }}</span></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Case Number</dt>
      <dd>{{ case_id }}</dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Brief Identifier</dt>
      <dd class="mono">{{ brief_id }}</dd>
    </div>
    {% if issuer_freezable %}
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Recoverable Asset</dt>
      <dd>{{ issuer_freezable.token }}<span class="secondary">issued by {{ issuer.short_name }}</span></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Freezable Holdings</dt>
      <dd>{{ issuer_freezable.total_usd_freezable }}<span class="secondary">across {{ issuer_freezable.freezable_count }} {{ "wallet" if issuer_freezable.freezable_count == 1 else "wallets" }} (status: FREEZABLE)</span></dd>
    </div>
    {% else %}
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Stolen Asset</dt>
      <dd>{{ asset.symbol }}<span class="secondary mono">{{ asset.contract }}</span></dd>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-meta-item">
      <dt>Initial Value</dt>
      {# v0.20.2 (audit-round-3 R3-3): see brief.py asset ctx. #}
      <dd>USD {{ asset.total_usd_value_at_theft if asset.is_multi_event else asset.usd_value_at_theft }}</dd>
    </div>
    {% endif %}
  </dl>
</section>

<div class="summary-box urgent">
  <p style="margin:0">
    {# v0.16.1 (audit follow-up): the summary box previously claimed
       "currently held" for ALL freezable modes, including
       historical_only — which would be a factual error for cases
       where the issuer's wallet RECEIVED the stolen tokens but no
       longer holds them. Now branched on evidence_mode parallel to
       the cover-title block at the top of the document. #}
    {% if issuer_freezable and issuer_freezable.evidence_mode == "historical_only" %}
    On {{ theft_event.timestamp_human }} UTC, {{ asset.amount_human }}
    {{ asset.symbol }} (USD {{ asset.total_usd_value_at_theft if asset.is_multi_event else asset.usd_value_at_theft }}{% if asset.is_multi_event %} across {{ asset.theft_event_count }} transactions{% endif %}) was removed from
    {{ victim.name }}'s wallet without authorization. Tracing through
    on-chain forwarding, a documented total of
    <strong>{{ issuer_freezable.total_usd_freezable }}</strong>
    in <strong>{{ issuer_freezable.token }}</strong> was received at
    {{ issuer_freezable.freezable_count }}
    {{ "wallet" if issuer_freezable.freezable_count == 1 else "wallets" }}
    under {{ issuer.short_name }}'s issuance authority during the
    documented theft trail. Current balances at those wallets may
    or may not remain — we are writing to request that
    {{ issuer.short_name }} investigate present-day disposition and
    apply a precautionary hold on any remaining balances, pending
    law-enforcement engagement.
    {% elif issuer_freezable and issuer_freezable.evidence_mode == "mixed" %}
    On {{ theft_event.timestamp_human }} UTC, {{ asset.amount_human }}
    {{ asset.symbol }} (USD {{ asset.total_usd_value_at_theft if asset.is_multi_event else asset.usd_value_at_theft }}{% if asset.is_multi_event %} across {{ asset.theft_event_count }} transactions{% endif %}) was removed from
    {{ victim.name }}'s wallet without authorization. After tracing
    through on-chain forwarding, stolen funds totaling
    <strong>{{ issuer_freezable.total_usd_freezable }}</strong>
    are currently held or were received as
    <strong>{{ issuer_freezable.token }}</strong>
    across {{ issuer_freezable.freezable_count }}
    {{ "wallet" if issuer_freezable.freezable_count == 1 else "wallets" }}
    under {{ issuer.short_name }}'s issuance authority — section 4
    details which addresses carry current-balance evidence vs.
    historical-receipt evidence.
    {% if issuer_freezable.has_investigate %}
    An additional
    {{ issuer_freezable.investigate_count }}
    {{ "wallet" if issuer_freezable.investigate_count == 1 else "wallets" }}
    (suspected, pending verification) are also identified in section 4.
    {% endif %}
    We are writing to request that {{ issuer.short_name }} place a
    precautionary hold on the current-balance
    {{ issuer_freezable.token }} positions and investigate the
    historical-receipt addresses listed below, pending
    law-enforcement engagement.
    {% elif issuer_freezable %}
    On {{ theft_event.timestamp_human }} UTC, {{ asset.amount_human }}
    {{ asset.symbol }} (USD {{ asset.total_usd_value_at_theft if asset.is_multi_event else asset.usd_value_at_theft }}{% if asset.is_multi_event %} across {{ asset.theft_event_count }} transactions{% endif %}) was removed from
    {{ victim.name }}'s wallet without authorization. After tracing through
    on-chain forwarding, stolen funds totaling
    <strong>{{ issuer_freezable.total_usd_freezable }}</strong>
    are currently held as <strong>{{ issuer_freezable.token }}</strong>
    across
    {{ issuer_freezable.freezable_count }}
    {{ "wallet" if issuer_freezable.freezable_count == 1 else "wallets" }}
    under {{ issuer.short_name }}'s issuance authority.
    {% if issuer_freezable.has_investigate %}
    An additional
    {{ issuer_freezable.investigate_count }}
    {{ "wallet" if issuer_freezable.investigate_count == 1 else "wallets" }}
    (suspected, pending verification) are also identified in section 4.
    {% endif %}
    We are writing to request that {{ issuer.short_name }} place a
    precautionary hold on the
    {{ issuer_freezable.token }} positions listed below, pending
    law-enforcement engagement.
    {% else %}
    On {{ theft_event.timestamp_human }} UTC, {{ asset.amount_human }}
    {{ asset.symbol }} (USD {{ asset.total_usd_value_at_theft if asset.is_multi_event else asset.usd_value_at_theft }}{% if asset.is_multi_event %} across {{ asset.theft_event_count }} transactions{% endif %}) was removed from
    {{ victim.name }}'s wallet without authorization and forwarded to
    <a class="mono" href="{{ current_holder.explorer_url }}">{{ current_holder.address }}</a>,
    where it remains as of {{ verified_at }} UTC. The recipient wallet has
    executed {{ outbound_count_of_stolen_asset }} outbound transfers of this
    asset since receipt. We are writing to request that {{ issuer.short_name }}
    place a precautionary hold on the position pending law-enforcement
    engagement.
    {% endif %}
  </p>
</div>

<h2>1. Victim Identification</h2>
<dl class="meta-grid">
  <dt>Name:</dt>            <dd>{{ victim.name }}</dd>
  {% if victim.citizenship %}<dt>Citizenship:</dt><dd>{{ victim.citizenship }}</dd>{% endif %}
  {% if victim.address %}<dt>Address:</dt><dd>{{ victim.address }}</dd>{% endif %}
  {% if victim.email %}<dt>Email:</dt>      <dd>{{ victim.email }}</dd>{% endif %}
  {% if victim.phone %}<dt>Phone:</dt>      <dd>{{ victim.phone }}</dd>{% endif %}
  <dt>Affected wallet:</dt> <dd><a class="mono" href="{{ victim_wallet_explorer_url }}">{{ victim.wallet_address }}</a></dd>
  {% if victim.legal_counsel %}
  <dt>Legal counsel:</dt><dd>{{ victim.legal_counsel }}{% if victim.legal_counsel_email %} &lt;{{ victim.legal_counsel_email }}&gt;{% endif %}</dd>
  {% endif %}
</dl>

{% if victim.incident_summary %}
<p>{{ victim.incident_summary }}</p>
{% endif %}

{% if issuer.kyc_required %}
<div class="summary-box action">
  <p style="margin:0">
    <strong>KYC asymmetry.</strong>
    {{ issuer.short_name }} required full KYC for the original
    {% if issuer_freezable %}{{ issuer_freezable.token }}{% else %}{{ asset.symbol }}{% endif %}
    subscription{% if issuer.kyc_minimum %} (minimum {{ issuer.kyc_minimum }}){% endif %}.
    {% if issuer_freezable %}
    The {{ issuer_freezable.total_count }} recipient
    {{ "wallet" if issuer_freezable.total_count == 1 else "wallets" }}
    listed in section 4 received these positions via direct on-chain
    transfer and have no corresponding KYC history. The disparity
    supports the basis for a precautionary hold.
    {% else %}
    {{ victim.name }} should appear in {{ issuer.short_name }}'s records as the
    KYC'd holder of this position. The recipient wallet at
    <a class="mono" href="{{ current_holder.explorer_url }}">{{ current_holder.address }}</a> has no
    corresponding KYC history; it received the position by direct on-chain
    transfer. The disparity supports the basis for a precautionary hold.
    {% endif %}
  </p>
</div>
{% endif %}

<h2>2. Theft Event</h2>
<table class="evidence">
  <tr><th>Date / time (UTC)</th><td class="mono">{{ theft_event.timestamp_human }}</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Block</th>             <td class="mono">{{ theft_event.block_number }}</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Transaction hash</th>  <td class="mono"><a href="{{ theft_event.explorer_url }}">{{ theft_event.tx_hash }}</a></td></tr>
  <tr><th>From (victim)</th>     <td class="mono victim-row"><a href="{{ theft_event.from_explorer_url }}">{{ theft_event.from_address }}</a></td></tr>
  <tr><th>To (perpetrator)</th>  <td class="mono perp-row"><a href="{{ theft_event.to_explorer_url }}">{{ theft_event.to_address }}</a></td></tr>
  <tr><th>Asset</th>             <td>{{ asset.symbol }} <span class="small">(contract: {% if asset_contract_explorer_url %}<a class="mono" href="{{ asset_contract_explorer_url }}">{{ asset.contract }}</a>{% else %}<span class="mono">{{ asset.contract }}</span>{% endif %})</span></td></tr>
  {# v0.20.2 (audit-round-3 R3-3): aggregate-across-events. #}
  <tr><th>Amount{% if asset.is_multi_event %} (total across {{ asset.theft_event_count }} events){% endif %}</th>            <td class="amount">{{ asset.total_amount_human if asset.is_multi_event else asset.amount_human }} {{ asset.symbol }}</td></tr>
  <tr><th>USD value at time of transaction</th><td class="amount">USD {{ asset.total_usd_value_at_theft if asset.is_multi_event else asset.usd_value_at_theft }}</td></tr>
  {% if asset.usd_value_current %}
  <tr><th>USD value (current estimate)</th>    <td class="amount">USD {{ asset.usd_value_current }}</td></tr>
  {% endif %}
</table>

<h2>3. Forwarding Chain (perpetrator's movements)</h2>
{% if hops %}
<p>After the theft, the funds moved through the following wallets controlled by the perpetrator:</p>
<table class="evidence">
  <tr>
    <th>Hop</th><th>Date (UTC)</th><th>Tx hash</th>
    <th>From</th><th>To</th><th>Amount</th>
  </tr>
  {% for hop in hops %}
  <tr>
    <td>{{ loop.index }}</td>
    <td class="mono">{{ hop.timestamp_human }}</td>
    <td class="mono"><a href="{{ hop.explorer_url }}">{{ hop.tx_hash[:14] }}…</a></td>
    <td class="mono perp-row"><a href="{{ hop.from_explorer_url }}">{{ hop.from_address }}</a></td>
    <td class="mono perp-row"><a href="{{ hop.to_explorer_url }}">{{ hop.to_address }}</a></td>
    <td class="amount">{{ hop.amount_human }} {{ hop.symbol }}</td>
  </tr>
  {% endfor %}
</table>
{% elif forwarding_observed %}
{# v0.20.1 (Jacob V-CFI01 residual #3): the linear hop chain is empty,
   but downstream destinations DID receive forwarded funds — they're
   enumerated in Section 4 below. Pre-v0.20.1 we printed "No subsequent
   forwarding observed" here, contradicting Section 4. #}
<p>
  The funds were forwarded from the initial receiving wallet
  through multiple downstream destinations rather than a single
  linear chain. Per-address current locations and inflow evidence
  are documented in Section 4 below.
</p>
{% else %}
<p>No subsequent forwarding observed; the funds remain in the perpetrator's initial receiving wallet.</p>
{% endif %}

{% if flow_filename %}
<p class="attachment-note">
  A complete fund-flow visualization is provided as a separate SVG
  attachment (<span class="mono">{{ flow_filename }}</span>) accompanying
  this letter. Open the file in any modern browser to inspect at full
  resolution; each wallet node links directly to its {{ primary_chain_explorer_name }} record.
</p>
{% endif %}

<h2>4. Current Location</h2>
{% if issuer_freezable %}
{# v0.16.1 (audit): preamble varies by evidence_mode. For
   historical_only mode "currently held" is a misstatement — the
   addresses received the funds, current disposition is what we're
   asking the issuer to determine. #}
{% if issuer_freezable.evidence_mode == "historical_only" %}
<p>
  Stolen funds were received as <strong>{{ issuer_freezable.token }}</strong>
  at the following {{ issuer_freezable.total_count }}
  {{ "wallet" if issuer_freezable.total_count == 1 else "wallets" }}
  under {{ issuer.short_name }}'s issuance authority during the
  documented theft trail. Current balances may have changed —
  per-address present-day disposition is what we are asking
  {{ issuer.short_name }} to verify. Each address links to its
  on-chain record for independent verification.
</p>
{% elif issuer_freezable.evidence_mode == "mixed" %}
<p>
  Stolen funds are currently held — or were received during the
  documented trail — as <strong>{{ issuer_freezable.token }}</strong>
  at the following {{ issuer_freezable.total_count }}
  {{ "wallet" if issuer_freezable.total_count == 1 else "wallets" }}
  under {{ issuer.short_name }}'s issuance authority. The Evidence
  column distinguishes addresses with confirmed current balances
  ("current") from addresses observed to receive the token in the
  trace ("historical"). Each address links to its on-chain record
  for independent verification.
</p>
{% else %}
<p>
  Stolen funds are currently held as
  <strong>{{ issuer_freezable.token }}</strong> at
  the following {{ issuer_freezable.total_count }}
  {{ "wallet" if issuer_freezable.total_count == 1 else "wallets" }}
  under {{ issuer.short_name }}'s issuance authority. Each address
  links to its on-chain record for independent verification.
</p>
{% endif %}
<table class="evidence">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th style="width:5em;">Status</th>
      <th style="width:6em;">Evidence</th>
      <th>Address</th>
      <th class="amount" style="width:11em;">Amount</th>
      <th class="amount" style="width:9em;">USD value</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    {# v0.20.2 (audit-round-3 R3-2): explicit branches per status so
       UNRECOVERABLE / EXCHANGE / TRANSIT rows are not silently
       mislabeled as INVESTIGATE. Same fix as le.html.j2 from
       audit-round-2 #10 — the issuer-facing letter had the bug
       too: every non-FREEZABLE row rendered with a red INVESTIGATE
       pill, including UNRECOVERABLE protocol contracts and
       EXCHANGE deposit addresses that the issuer's compliance
       team would (correctly) bin as not their problem. The
       resulting credibility hit on an issuer letter is much
       worse than the LE one — the issuer can call us out by
       saying "row 4 isn't a real freeze target, why is it on
       your INVESTIGATE list?" #}
    {% for h in issuer_freezable.holdings %}
    <tr>
      <td>
        {% if h.status == 'FREEZABLE' %}
        <span class="label-pill" style="color:#2F6B3E;">FREEZABLE</span>
        {% elif h.status == 'INVESTIGATE' %}
        <span class="label-pill" style="color:#7C2D12;">INVESTIGATE</span>
        {% elif h.status == 'UNRECOVERABLE' %}
        <span class="label-pill" style="color:#6B7280;">UNRECOVERABLE</span>
        {% elif h.status == 'EXCHANGE' %}
        <span class="label-pill" style="color:#1E40AF;">EXCHANGE</span>
        {% elif h.status == 'TRANSIT' %}
        <span class="label-pill" style="color:#92400E;">TRANSIT</span>
        {% else %}
        <span class="label-pill" style="color:#6B7280;">{{ h.status or 'UNKNOWN' }}</span>
        {% endif %}
      </td>
      <td>
        {# v0.14.9: surface evidence-type per row so the issuer's
           compliance team can act differently on each: current-balance
           rows freeze NOW; historical-inflow rows freeze IF balance
           remains and otherwise help trace onward. #}
        {% if h.evidence_type == 'historical_inflow' %}
        <span class="label-pill" style="color:#92400E;">historical</span>
        {% else %}
        <span class="label-pill" style="color:#1E40AF;">current</span>
        {% endif %}
      </td>
      <td class="mono"><a href="{{ h.explorer_url }}">{{ h.address }}</a></td>
      <td class="amount mono">{{ h.amount }}</td>
      <td class="amount mono">{{ h.usd }}</td>
    </tr>
    {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>
<div class="summary-box action">
  <p style="margin:0;">
    <strong>Totals:</strong>
    {{ issuer_freezable.total_usd_freezable }} confirmed FREEZABLE
    {% if issuer_freezable.has_investigate %}
    · {{ issuer_freezable.total_usd_suspected }} including positions still under
    investigation
    {% endif %}
    · Last verified {{ verified_at }} UTC
    · Freeze capability: <strong>{{ issuer_freezable.freeze_capability }}</strong>
  </p>
</div>
{% else %}
<div class="summary-box action">
  <p style="margin:0 0 0.4em 0;">
    {{ asset.amount_human }} {{ asset.symbol }} held at:
  </p>
  <p class="mono" style="font-size:11pt; margin:0 0 0.7em;"><a href="{{ current_holder.explorer_url }}">{{ current_holder.address }}</a></p>
  <p style="margin:0;">
    <a href="{{ current_holder.explorer_url }}">View on {{ primary_chain_explorer_name }}</a>
    &nbsp;·&nbsp;
    <a href="{{ current_holder.explorer_url }}#tokentxns">Token transfer history</a>
    <br/>
    Last verified {{ verified_at }} UTC.
    Outbound transfers of this asset since receipt: {{ outbound_count_of_stolen_asset }}.
  </p>
</div>
{% endif %}

<h2>5. Specific Request</h2>
<p>
  We ask that {{ issuer.name }}:
</p>
<ol>
  {% if issuer_freezable and issuer_freezable.evidence_mode == "historical_only" %}
  {# v0.14.9: pure-historical letter — addresses received the token
     at some point but current balance may be zero. Lead with the
     investigative cooperation ask, then the contingent freeze ask. #}
  <li>
    Review the
    {{ issuer_freezable.historical_count }} {{ "address" if issuer_freezable.historical_count == 1 else "addresses" }}
    listed in section 4 against your internal records.
    {{ issuer_freezable.token }} issued by {{ issuer.short_name }} was
    documented as received at these addresses
    {% if issuer_freezable.earliest_observed %}
    beginning on or about {{ issuer_freezable.earliest_observed[:10] }}
    {% endif %}
    as part of the underlying theft.
  </li>
  <li>
    Indicate, in writing and to the extent your records permit, the
    onward disposition of the {{ issuer_freezable.token }} received at
    these addresses — in particular whether any portion was redeemed
    into a {{ issuer.short_name }}-controlled account associated with a
    KYC'd customer, whether {{ issuer.short_name }} retains
    custody-equivalent records of subsequent on-chain transfers, and any
    further compliance flags your team has placed on these addresses.
  </li>
  <li>
    Place a precautionary hold on any {{ issuer_freezable.token }}
    balance that remains at the addresses listed in section 4, in effect
    until law enforcement authorities representing the victim have
    engaged.
  </li>
  {% elif issuer_freezable %}
  <li>
    Place a precautionary hold on the
    {{ issuer_freezable.token }} positions listed in section 4
    {% if issuer_freezable.has_freezable %}
    — specifically, the
    {{ issuer_freezable.freezable_count }} {{ "address" if issuer_freezable.freezable_count == 1 else "addresses" }}
    marked <strong>FREEZABLE</strong> totaling
    {{ issuer_freezable.total_usd_freezable }}
    {% endif %}
    — in effect until law enforcement authorities representing the
    victim have engaged.
    {% if issuer_freezable.has_investigate %}
    For the {{ issuer_freezable.investigate_count }}
    {{ "address" if issuer_freezable.investigate_count == 1 else "addresses" }}
    marked <strong>INVESTIGATE</strong>, we ask that {{ issuer.short_name }}
    review the corresponding KYC / subscription history and indicate
    whether the position can be added to the hold.
    {% endif %}
    {% if issuer_freezable.evidence_mode == "mixed" and issuer_freezable.historical_count > 0 %}
    For the {{ issuer_freezable.historical_count }}
    {{ "address" if issuer_freezable.historical_count == 1 else "addresses" }}
    documented under <strong>historical-inflow</strong> evidence
    (see section 4), please additionally indicate the onward
    disposition of {{ issuer_freezable.token }} received at those
    addresses.
    {% endif %}
  </li>
  {% else %}
  <li>
    Place a precautionary hold on redemption of the
    {{ asset.amount_human }} {{ asset.symbol }} position at
    <a class="mono" href="{{ current_holder.explorer_url }}">{{ current_holder.address }}</a>,
    in effect until law enforcement authorities representing the victim
    have engaged.
  </li>
  {% endif %}
  <li>
    Confirm receipt of this request in writing and record the date and
    time of notice.
  </li>
  <li>
    Identify a point of contact for coordination with the relevant
    authorities, who we expect to follow with formal process.
  </li>
  {% if issuer.kyc_required %}
  <li>
    {% if issuer_freezable %}
    Verify internally whether {{ victim.name }} is the KYC'd subscriber
    of record for any of the {{ issuer_freezable.token }} positions
    listed in section 4. The result need not be shared externally; we
    ask only that {{ issuer.short_name }} confirm the review has been
    performed.
    {% else %}
    Verify internally whether {{ victim.name }} is the KYC'd subscriber
    of record for the affected position. The result need not be shared
    externally; we ask only that {{ issuer.short_name }} confirm the
    review has been performed.
    {% endif %}
  </li>
  {% endif %}
</ol>
<p>
  We are not alleging any wrongdoing on the part of {{ issuer.name }}.
  This request is made because {{ issuer.short_name }}'s protocol-level
  authority is the only avenue by which the stolen position can be
  preserved before further dissipation occurs.
</p>

{% if issuer.regulatory_framework %}
<h2>6. Regulatory Context</h2>
<p>
  {{ issuer.name }} operates under {{ issuer.regulatory_framework }}.
  Cooperation with a precautionary hold pending law-enforcement engagement
  is consistent with the consumer- and investor-protection obligations
  embedded in that framework.
</p>
{% endif %}

<h2>7. Verification</h2>
<p>
  Every fact in this brief is drawn from public on-chain data and is
  independently verifiable. Each transaction hash links to its
  {{ primary_chain_explorer_name }} record. As of {{ verified_at }} UTC, the recipient wallet shows
  {{ outbound_count_of_stolen_asset }} outbound transfers of
  {{ asset.symbol }}.
</p>
<p class="small">
  Sources: {{ primary_chain_explorer_name }} API; CoinGecko historical pricing; our internal
  cross-case label database.
</p>

